I'm just trying to get some ideas that could cause &quot;Speak to&quot; to not work and print the &quot;invalid command&quot; message.  I've checked my synonyms for 'speak' or 'speak to,' I have no Game verbs listed, and no Game Command or Room Command uses the word 'speak' or 'speak to'; therefore, there's no confliction occurring with the term 'speak' or 'speak to.'

Ok, here's the code for an object I've been testing &quot;Speak to&quot; on... I don't think you'll find anything wrong here, but to list code for my whole game would not coincide with a proper post length... Object name, alias name, and procedure name are dumbed up for quick viewing... Also, it should be mentioned, the [i:2dyhujrg]look[/i:2dyhujrg] message executes perfectly, along with the procedures listed below....

[code:2dyhujrg]
	define object &lt;Object_Name&gt;
		alias &lt;Alias_Name&gt;
		look msg &lt;Text here!&gt;
		take do &lt;Take_Procedure&gt;
		speak &lt;Text here!&gt;
		displaytype &lt;display_text&gt;
		article &lt;it&gt;
		gender &lt;it&gt;
		drop do &lt;Drop_Procedure&gt;
	end define
[/code:2dyhujrg]
